The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Feb. 22: The sensex tumbled by 167.18 points on fag-end selling, extending losses for the third straight session. Selling was not confined to any particular sector as all the sectorial indices finished in the negative terrain. Banking and pharma counters were the prominent losers. Operators and high networth individuals played safe before the announcement of the Union budget on February 28.

 Mumbai, Feb. 22: Firstsource Solutions today made a strong debut on the stock exchanges. Against the offer price of Rs 64 per share, Firstsource opened at Rs 90.10 on the NSE, a premium of 40.78 per cent. The share, however, surrendered some of its gains later in the day.

 New Delhi, Feb. 22: Max India Ltd (MIL) proposes to raise Rs 1,000 crore for expansion. It plans to issue equity to qualified institutional buyers for Rs 1,000 crore in one or more tranches.

 New Delhi, Feb. 22: Shoppers Stop has joined hands with international airport retailer, the Nuance group, to offer duty-free retail products at domestic airports. 

 New Delhi, Feb. 22: Hutchison Telecom International Ltd (HTIL) has said Essar did not have the right to match the British firms bid. The Ruias, however, contested the claim.




